Daily Report 
<DATE1>  19 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prices of Gold, U.S. Dollar Increase </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prices of Gold, U.S. Dollar Increase </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2104094994 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2104094994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It is noteworthy in today's market prices that the 
gold price increased by 1,000 dong per ounce in the south while 
in the north the price decreased. The U.S. dollar increased by 
10 to 20 dong per dollar in the north and the value of Chinese 
currencies is also higher than the previous day in Lang Son 
Province and Hanoi. 
  Rice in Ca Mau is 1,100 dong per kg, while in My Tho it is 
50 
dong cheaper. The price of agricultural products in central 
Vietnam is normal while the price of construction materials has 
increased in the north and decreased in the south. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

