<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fighting Reported Inside Cambodia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fighting Reported Inside Cambodia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2204081294 Bangkok THAI RAT in Thai 22 Apr 94 p 22 </F>
<F P=103> BK2204081294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok THAI RAT </F>
<F P=105>  Thai </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] There was a report of heavy shelling inside 
Cambodia opposite Sa Kaeo Province on 21 April. According to 
the report, a group of about 200 Khmer Rouge forces of the 519th 
Division at 0500 on 21 April opened fire on a former Khmer Serei 
command post, which is now under control of the Cambodian 
Government, at Boeng Ta Kuan in Thmar Puok District, Banteay 
Meanchey Province, about 20 km from Ta Phraya District, Sa Kaeo 
Province. As a result, people's houses and markets were 
damaged; government soldiers were running away from the attack. 
The shelling continued until afternoon. About 600 Cambodian 
people, mainly children and the elderly, crossed the border into 
Thailand's Ban Khlong Phaeng, Tambon Thapsadet, Taphraya 
District. Thai soldiers and policemen disarmed them and gave 
them help on humanitarian grounds. General Atchawin 
Sawetserani, Burapha Task Force deputy commander, ordered that a 
temporary shelter be given to those people until the fighting 
inside Cambodia calms down. They will be pushed back once the 
shelling stops. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

