fighters-bomber and assault fighters, flying between Oeyon 
island and Taehuksan island until dawn of the next day. 
  This war exercise, which was frantically staged under the 
cover of fighters from U.S. air bases in Japan, was aimed at 
improving the capability of nighttime airborne refueling to 
airplanes mobilized from overseas air bases and long-range 
airplanes belonging to the U.S. Air Forces unit in South Korea 
and the puppet Air Force for a northward invasion. 

