<H3> <TI>   Al-Qadhdhafi Denounces U.S. `Nuclear Threat' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Qadhdhafi Denounces U.S. `Nuclear Threat' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2204045594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0430 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2204045594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- Colonel Mu'ammar 
al-Qadhdhafi, leader of the great September First Revolution of 
the Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya, denounced 
the nuclear threat of the United States to the DPRK at the 
second lawyers conference of Libya held in Tarabulus over April 
14-16. 
  In his speech he charged that the United States was using 
the 
United Nations as a tool for suppressing the people and abusing 
it for the attainment of its aims. "The confrontation today is a 
confrontation with imperialism," he said. 
  Saying he did not pin any hope on the UN Charter which had 
already been violated and destroyed, he went on: 
  "Has North Korea occupied Kuwait? Or has it reached the 
nuclear arms on the earth? Is this the reason why they abuse 
and threaten North Korea and attempt to strike it? Aren't they 
going too far? 
  "We must fight a bloody fight against imperialism. We will 
fight to the last man to defend our rights." 

</TEXT>

