<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 21 (KCNA) -- Leaders and parties of 
different countries expressed full support to the Korean 
people's cause of national reunification and their efforts for a 
peaceful solution of the nuclear issue. 
  Meles Zenawi, president of the transitional Government of 
Ethiopia, when he met a DPRK Government delegation on April 15, 
expressed solidarity for the struggle of the Korean people to 
achieve an independent and peaceful reunification of their 
country, and supported the DPRK's stand to solve the nuclear 
issue of the Korean peninsula peacefully through DPRK-USA talks. 
  Prime Minister of Uganda George Kosmas Adyebo when he met a 
delegation of the DPRK Foreign Ministry on April 14, expressed 
support and solidarity for the just cause of the Korean 
Government and people for the reunification of the country by 
means of confederacy. He said he firmly supports Korea's stand 
to peacefully solve the nuclear issue of the Korean peninsula 
through the DPRK-USA talks. 
  Antoine Malonga, chairman of the Congolese Movement for the 
Construction of New Society, when he received the DPRK 
ambassador to his country on April 9, denounced the anti- 
socialist, anti-DPRK moves of the United States and its 
satellite forces and expressed full support to the self- 
defensive measures of the DPRK. 
  The world will see a great victory of the Korean-style 
socialism, he stressed. 
  Valeri Sklatov, chairman of the Liberal Patriotic Party for 
the "Rebirth" of Russia, when he met with the DPRK ambassador on 
April 7, expressed full support to the DPRK's stand on the 
nuclear issue and denounced intrigues of the United States. 
  The secretariat of the Central Committee of the Socialist 
Party of Australia in a statement April 11 urged the United 
States to stop its threats and pressure on the DPRK at once and 
implement the policy based on non-interference in the internal 
affairs of sovereign states. 

</TEXT>

