<H3> <TI>   `Big Efforts' To Improve Agriculture Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Big Efforts' To Improve Agriculture Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2204053594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0457 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2204053594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- Korea is putting big 
efforts into agricultural production this year, too. 
  According to the state budget for 1994, a huge amount of 
fund, or up 6 percent from last year, will go to the 
agricultural sector. 
  This year, Korea will consolidate the achievements of the 
rural technical revolution which has been completed in the main 
and bring its might into full play and further expand and 
develop the successes in mechanization and extensive application 
of chemicals in keeping with the high level of irrigation and 
electrification. 
  Many farm machines of various kinds are supplied to the 
countryside to develop the comprehensive mechanization of 
agriculture to a higher level. Only recently, 500 tractors and 
250 trucks were supplied at a time to Chongdan, Yonan and 
Paechon Counties. 
  Large quantities of various chemical fertilizers are 
produced 
and supplied as well. 
  Last year, the state allocated funds, or up 2.8 percent from 
the previous year, to agriculture. 
  One of the most important successes registered in the 
countryside of Korea last year is that an unusual bumper harvest 
was reaped even under the unfavorable weather conditions. 

</TEXT>

