<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Release of New Scientific Films Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Release of New Scientific Films Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2104105194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1004 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2104105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 21 (KCNA) -- Several scientific 
films have been released of late by the Korean scientific and 
educational film studio. 
  The scientific film "Lactic Acid Drink Made of Water 
Strained 
Off Coagulating Bean Curd" introduces an easy method of making 
the drink. 
  The water in which bean is swollen and the water strained 
off 
coagulating bean curd contain different kinds of nutritious 
ingredients. When they are fermented by putting lactobacilli 
into them, they are turned into a good lactic acid drink. 
  It is good for daily drinking and is highly effective in 
promoting the digestive functions and preventing and curing 
colitis and other diseases. 
  The scientific film "Magnet and Fur" shows the mechanism of 
the device of cleaning fur from boilers, telling it will pay off 
profusely if it is installed at all places where fur forms. 
  Besides, the studio has made scientific films of different 
themes such as "Production of Methane in Winter", "Calcining Egg 
Coal", "King Tongmyong and His Tomb" and "Taekwon-do and Health". 

</TEXT>

