<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Children's Garden at Mangyongdae Described </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Children's Garden at Mangyongdae Described </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2104215894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1506 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2104215894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 21 (KCNA) -- All kinds of flowers 
are in full bloom and trees grow green at the April 15 
children's flower garden as spring came. The flower garden 
covers an area of more than 100 hectares around the Mangyongdae 
school children's palace in Pyongyang. 
  It was opened in April, 1992. 
  Tens of thousands of trees and 50,000 plants of flowers of 
more than 130 kinds from all parts of the country and many 
countries of the world have taken roots, giving off fragrance. 
  The garden serves as a fine base for the cultural and 
emotional life of the school youth and children and working 
people, as a base for botanical education. 

</TEXT>

