<H3> <TI>   Plot To Kill Communist Chief Denied by Military </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Plot To Kill Communist Chief Denied by Military </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2204091394 Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network in Tagalog 
0500 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2204091394 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Tagalog </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The military leadership today denied involvement 
in a plot to liquidate Jose Ma. Sison, exiled leader of the 
Communist Party of the Philippines-New People's Army-National 
Democratic Front [CPP-NPA-NDF]. This was revealed by Lieutenant 
General Arturo Enrile, Armed Forces of the Philippines [AFP] 
chief of staff, and Maj. Gen. Alfredo Filler, AFP vice chief of 
staff, in reaction to Sison's accusation. 
  Enrile emphasized that any attempt on the life of any of the 
communist movement's leaders will only destroy the peace process 
pushed by government. 
  Meanwhile, Filler said that there is no report of any such 
plan monitored by the AFP Intelligence Service. Filler 
clarified that it is Sison's group who are doing things that are 
destructive to them in the first place, like murder, kidnapping, 
and robbery. 
  [Begin recording in English] [Enrile] Why should we do that 
in the first place. You know, we are part of that sincere 
effort for peace in this country. If that is done, that will 
only derail whatever peace process that we are working out with 
the CPP-NPA-NDF. So, there is really no such thing. 
  [Filler] The Armed Forces of the Philippines do not operate 
that way. We view such an act as entirely counterproductive to 
the reconciliation process and our search for lasting peace. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

