<H3> <TI>   Priest Assumes Leadership of Pro-Sison NPA </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Priest Assumes Leadership of Pro-Sison NPA </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2004123994 Manila THE MANILA CHRONICLE in English 11 Apr 
94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> BK2004123994 </F>
<F P=104>  Manila THE MANILA CHRONICLE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bacolod City -- A ranking New People's Army (NPA) 
official has confirmed that priest-turned-rebel Frank Fernandez 
has assumed leadership of the pro-Sison forces in Negros. 
  The rejectionist group of rebels under Arturo Tabara, 
however, described the leadership of Fernandez as "fake" and 
said it is not recognized by the NPA forces in Negros. 
  Fernandez is the secretary general of the National 
Democratic 
Front. 
  Estelito Dioquino, former NPA commander of Southern Negros, 
claimed majority of the NPA forces in Negros are supporters of 
the rejectionist group under Tabara, alias Victor del Mar, 
Communist Party of the Philippines Visayas Commission chairman. 

