<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vientiane-Vangviang Section of Highway Completed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vientiane-Vangviang Section of Highway Completed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2204070094 Vientiane KPL in English 0921 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2204070094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, April 21 (KPL) -- The construction of 
the 156 km Vientiane-Vangviang section of road 13 north 
undertaken by the Road No.10 Construction Company is now 
completed. 
  The director of the road construction company, Mr. Savat 
Nokeo said that the construction project of the road section 
cost 15 million U.S. dollars, which was a loan from the World 
Bank. He said his company conducted the construction for three 
years. 
  He also said that his company was continuing with the 
construction of the 60 km Vangvieng-Kasi section of the same 
road. In addition, he said his company had received a contract 
from Tianjin Company of China, the contractor of road 13 south, 
for work on a long section of the road from Pak Kading to 
Savannakhet. 

</TEXT>

