<H3> <TI>   Hata Gives Statement on Candidacy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hata Gives Statement on Candidacy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2204103594 Tokyo NHK General Television Network in 
Japanese 0622 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2204103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NHK General Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by Shinseito leader Tsutomu Hata at a joint news </F>
conference with unidentified correspondents at the Diet building 
in Tokyo -- live] 
  [Text] [Hata] This is Tsutomu Hata. As has just been 
announced by the coalition leaders, I have been selected from 
among the coalition party leaders, including Social Democratic 
Party of Japan [SDPJ] Chairman Tomiichi Murayama, as a candidate 
to be the new prime minister of the coalition's second 
administration. 
  Frankly speaking, I do not think I am a capable man, and 
cannot help feeling some hesitation in accepting the serious 
responsibilities over state affairs. However, since the 
coalition leaders have been trying so hard to reach a 
conclusion, I have to take upon myself the hair-raising 
responsibilities as top leader of the nation. Thus, I have 
decided to accept the candidacy. 
  As Murayama just noted, the coalition has worked out a 
multiparty memorandum on a policy accord for forming a new 
coalition government. When I am approved as the new prime 
minister through Diet elections, I will try my best, in line 
with the policy accord, to make Japan a sound nation where 
everybody can live in comfort. Also, I will seek the 
high-quality nation advocated by Hosokawa. 
  Another point is that, as other coalition leaders have 
stated, Japan must become a trustworthy, understandable, and 
beloved nation in the international community. I would like to 
try my best to achieve these objectives. 
  I sincerely seek the understanding of the public. Thank you 
very much. 

</TEXT>

