<H3> <TI>   Takemura on Hata Cooperation Request </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Takemura on Hata Cooperation Request </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2204134894 Tokyo NHK General Television Network in 
Japanese 1006 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2204134894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NHK General Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video; from "NHK News 7" program] </F>
  [Text] Foreign Minister Tsutomu Hata held meetings with 
Masayoshi Takemura, chairman of Sakigake [Harbinger], and 
leaders of New Party Mirai [Future] and Jiyuto [Liberal Party] 
to ask for their cooperation with the new administration. 
Sakigake plans to support the government from outside the 
cabinet. New Party Mirai and Jiyuto have recently been formed 
by defectors from the Liberal Democratic Party [LDP]. 
  Takemura offered the following comments: 
  [Begin recording] These matters are confirmed. I agree with 
the new administration's intention to continue with and further 
the reform efforts undertaken by the Hosokawa administration. 
As to particulars about policies, I have my own views regarding 
the finer details, but I told Hata I agree in general with the 
policies worked out among the coalition parties. [end recording] 
  The leaders of New Party Mirai and Jiyuto made the following 
comments: 
  [Begin recording] [Michihiko Kano, head of New Party Mirai; 
identified by caption] Since we appraise Foreign Minister Hata 
for such matters as his basic political stance, I told him we 
would give our cooperation. 
  [Koji Kakizawa, head of Jiyuto; identified by caption] Since 
Hata asked for our cooperation, I told him I look forward to 
giving him a definite answer after discussing the matter with 
lower house members who are my Jiyuto comrades. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

