<H3> <TI>   Kono on `Double Power Structure' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kono on `Double Power Structure' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2204131094 Tokyo NHK General Television Network in 
Japanese 1008 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2204131094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NHK General Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video: from "NHK News 7" program] </F>
  [Text] Liberal Democratic Party President Yohei Kono 
stresses his determination to have a showdown with the new 
administration. 
  [Begin recording] I feel this is a Shinseito [Japan Renewal 
Party] administration. If we asked Hata what he thinks of being 
a candidate for the premiership, he would answer that he is a 
player while another person writes the scenarios. Well, I 
cannot help saying that the coalition still has a double power 
structure. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

