<H3> <TI>   Ship Export Reportedly Increases in FY 1993 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ship Export Reportedly Increases in FY 1993 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2004124294 Tokyo KYODO in English 1136 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2004124294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 20 KYODO -- Japan's ship export 
contracts in fiscal 1993 totaled 197 vessels of 7,471,018 gross 
tons, the second highest in 10 years and 2.8 times more than the 
previous year, the Japan Ship Exporters Association said 
Wednesday [20 April]. The association said the highest figure 
in the 10-year period was 8.04 million tons in fiscal 1989. 
  The increase for fiscal 1993, which ended March 31, 1994, 
was 
chiefly due to more orders for bulk ships, which recovered to a 
3.3 percent growth from fiscal 1991 levels after a sharp drop in 
orders in fiscal 1992 because of the world recession, an 
association official said. 
  The contracts included 125 bulk ships of 3.75 million tons 
and 21 tankers of 2.11 million tons, it said. 

</TEXT>

