<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Oil Exploration Contract Signed With U.S, Japan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Oil Exploration Contract Signed With U.S, Japan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2204022194 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
2300 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2204022194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Hanoi on the afternoon of 19 April, Dr. Ho Si 
Thoang, general director of the Vietnam Oil and Gas Corporation 
[VOGC], signed a production-sharing contract with 
representatives of the U.S. (NJP) Group and Japanese companies 
for oil and gas exploration and exploitation in Lot 05-1B on the 
Vietnamese continental shelf. Participating in the contract are 
the VOGC's Oil and Gas Exploration and Exploitation Company and 
an oil and gas company of the Russian Federation. This is 27th 
production-sharing contract signed between the VOGC and foreign 
companies since the introduction of the state Investment Law; it 
is the first contract signed with a major U.S. oil company. 
  Lot 05-1B in the Thanh Long oil field is located on the 
Vietnamese continental shelf. It lies about 400 km southeast of 
the Vietnamese coast next to the Dai Hung oil field. It is 
considered a promising spot for oil and gas. The U.S company 
searched and explored here in early 1975 before withdrawing in 
April 1975. 
  Present at the signing ceremony were Deputy Prime Minister 
Tran Duc Luong, many high-ranking Vietnamese Government 
officials, and diplomatic representatives of the concerned 
countries. 

</TEXT>

