<H3> <TI>   Japan-U.S. Meeting on Cooperation Denounced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japan-U.S. Meeting on Cooperation Denounced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2204105394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1040 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2204105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Dangerous Military Tieup" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- Japanese and U.S. 
brasshats met in Tokyo recently to discuss "the Japan-U.S. 
cooperation system for coping with a possible dispute on the 
Korean peninsula." 
  NODONG SINMUN today views this as a clear proof that the 
U.S. 
and Japanese reactionaries, in league with each other, are 
proceeding with designs of aggression and domination on Korea 
and other Asian countries. 
  They regard aggression on Korea as the key to achieving 
military upperhand and supremacy in Asia, the analyst says, and 
continues: 
  The United States is intending to stifle the DPRK by using 
the Japanese territory and its military and economic potentials, 
while the Japanese reactionaries are scheming to convert Japan 
into a military power in a short period and gratify their desire 
to stage a comeback to Korea by cooperating with the United 
States in the execution of its policy. 
  It must not go unnoticed that the Japanese reactionaries are 
openly revealing their design to reinvade Korea, charging the 
DPRK with "nuclear development" and "missile threat" at a time 
when the United States has intensified the anti-DPRK campaign to 
stifle it as never before. 
  It is a lie to describe the Japan-based U.S. Forces as 
something for "Japan-U.S. security." They have been deployed 
according to the U.S. aggressive strategy of forward deployment. 
Their basic mission and duty are to play the role of a shock 
brigade in the execution of the U.S. policy of aggression and 
war against the DPRK and other Asian nations. 
  The U.S. and Japanese reactionaries must give up their 
criminal military tieup and aggressive moves against the DPRK 
and other Asian nations. 

</TEXT>

