<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Boeng Trakuon Base Said Liberated 21 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Boeng Trakuon Base Said Liberated 21 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2204024294 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2204024294 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>

<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Here is a report on the attack and liberation of 
Boeng Trakuon and its vicinity: 
  1. Boeng Trakuon, also called Banteay Mean Rit, is an 
important area from which UNTAC [UN Transitional Authority in 
Cambodia], the United States, and an alliance used artillery 
pieces and tanks to attack Phnum Prak hill in the Phnum Chhat 
area in August 1993. 
  2. After the attack, the two-headed government, the United 
States, the alliance, and the communist Vietnamese assigned the 
8th division of U.S.-backed puppet Dien Del [former chief of 
staff of the Khmer People's National Liberation Armed Forces] to 
join the 7th and 8th divisions of the communist Vietnamese 
puppets. 
  3. The 7th, 8th, and 12th divisions joined the communist 
Vietnamese puppets' troops to attack the Malai and Pailin 
regions. [sentence as heard] In February and March 1994, the 
United States provided the Dien Del forces with more than 1,000 
tonnes of armaments and ammunition bought from the communist 
Vietnamese and Russia. 
  4. After clearly grasping the situation, the people and 
National Army of Democratic Kampuchea mustered forces to attack 
the warmongering troops and destroyers of the nation at Boeng 
Trakuon called Banteay Mean Rit, the biggest base of Dien Del. 
  On the night between 20 and 21 April, the people and NADK 
attacked and completely liberated Boeng Takuon and its vicinity. 
The area, which is a major base of U.S.-backed puppets Dien Del 
and Pan Thai, was totally destroyed. In the wake of the attack, 
the people in the area raised their hands praying and said: 
Down with the notorious border bandits, Down with the great 
assassins. As for parasoldiers [of the Khmer People's National 
Liberation Armed Forces], they also shouted: Down with great 
border bandits Dien Del and Pan Thai, who plunder the people's 
cattle and send them across the border. 

</TEXT>

