<H3> <TI>   New Administration Urged To Seek UNSC Seat </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Administration Urged To Seek UNSC Seat </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2104053494 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 21 
Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2104053494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 21 April Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] With regard to the question of Japan's permanent 
membership on the UN Security Council [UNSC], a top Foreign 
Ministry official said on 20 April: "If we do not join the 
UNSC, there are various kinds of information that we cannot 
obtain. In order to play an active role, Japan should attain 
permanent membership on its own initiative rather than wait for 
other nations' recommendations." He thus indicated that with 
the inauguration of the new administration, Japan should 
demonstrate an even more positive attitude than that of the 
Hosokawa administration. 

</TEXT>

