BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 19 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
statement issued by the MSDP [Mongolian Social Democratic Party] 
applying to the parliament of Mongolia and government notes the 
complicated political situation in the country due to a complete 
ignorance by the parliament and government of the numerous 
demands for the resignation of the government on the part of the 
MDA [Mongolian Democratic Association], UMS [Union of Mongolian 
Students] UNP [Union for New Progress] and MSDP. The life of 
some 39 people announced a hunger strike for the future of the 
country is endangering. [sentence as received] Joining in the 
political struggle for justice by a leader of the MSDP and MP 
[member of parliament] R. Gonchigdorj is an unprecedented event 
not ever met before in the states of democracy. 
  The responsibility for the aftermath of the present crisis, 
the statement says, lies in the Great State Hural and government. 

</TEXT>

