  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 20 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- According 
to the Parliamentary Press Office, the Great State Hural has 
discussed the demands of the Mongolian Democratic Association 
(MDA) for resignation of the government which members are being 
accused of being involved in corruption. Such accusations were 
also brought against some members of the parliament. The Great 
State Hural has decided to consider this issue after proper 
juridical bodies where the case is under investigation would 
pass their verdict. The Parliamentary Press Office notes that 
the Great State Hural has set up a working group for elaborating 
the draft law on legitimate status of the members of the 
parliament. 

