<H3> <TI>   Association Meets To Support Counterstrikers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Association Meets To Support Counterstrikers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1904183894 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1243 GMT 19 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1904183894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 19 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- In protest 
against the political strike announced at the Suhbaatar Square a 
meeting has been held to support those being on a counter strike 
at the Freedom Square. The meeting was organized by the "281" 
Association for Protection of Independence of Mongolia. 
  Speaking at the meeting Z. Dorj, a writer said that the 
political crisis being deepening in Mongolia might be leading to 
the edge of a great confrontation and expressed the support by 
the supporters of the association to the Government of Mongolia 
and the Prime Minister P. Jasray's activities. Members of the 
parliament T. Nyamhainyambuu M. Zenee and a writer B. Dogmid in 
their speeches condemned the actions of the opposition and 
expressed their full support of the activities of the government 
as well. 
  Also chief of a department of the General Police Board 
Garamjil addressing the meeting said that the police are not to 
serve any of the two opposing political forces announced a 
hunger strike and can declare with a full responsibility for 
their words that they would do their best in order to protect 
Mongolian citizens from any harm, acting within the frameworks 
of the law. 

</TEXT>

