<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 20 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
meeting which was supposed to be held today on the initiative of 
the Mongolian Movement of Voters at the Erh Choloonii Square in 
the Mongolian capital has not been held. The reason for that is 
not being released. 
  The Mongolian Movement of Voters has issued yesterday a 
statement in connection with the current complicated situation 
in the country arising due to the political hunger strike taken 
at the Suhbaatar Square. 
  The statement by the movement demanded the Mongolian 
Government to carry out a nationwide referendum on the issue of 
vote of confidence in the Great State Hural. The movement also 
urged to set up a commission for national concord intended for 
creation proper conditions for well-being of the people and all 
the electorate of Mongolia, developing a democratic political 
system and establishing social justice. 

