<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 19 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Completing 
his official visit to Mongolia the Governor General of Australia 
Bill Hayden has spoken at the session of the Mongolian 
parliament. 
  My current visit to Mongolia which is the first one is a 
manifestation of developing recently close contacts between the 
two countries. In this respect I would like to say addressing 
the members of the Mongolian parliament that Australia has been 
and is supporting the democratic renovations in Mongolia. We 
are appreciating the fact that Mongolia is striving to expand 
her relations with the countries of the Asian and Pacific 
region. We Australians are greeting the peaceful transition of 
the country to democracy, said in his speech Bill Hayden. 
