<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   IAEA Responds to DPRK Regarding Fuel Rods </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IAEA Responds to DPRK Regarding Fuel Rods </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2204005494 Seoul HANGUK ILBO in Korean 22 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK2204005494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul HANGUK ILBO </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On the afternoon of 21 April, Hans Blix, director 
general of the International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA], sent a 
message to North Korea expressing the IAEA position on North 
Korea's proposal for the IAEA to witness the exchange of nuclear 
fuel bars at its nuclear facilities. 
  It has been learned that Director General Blix said that the 
witnessing of IAEA inspectors of the exchange of nuclear fuel 
bars should be technically and perfectly carried out without any 
obstruction. He also said the inspection of the radiochemical 
laboratory, which was not carried out during the past 
inspections, should be fully resumed as well. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

