<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister: Security Plans Need My Approval </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister: Security Plans Need My Approval </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2104113594 Seoul YONHAP in English 1126 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2104113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 21 (YONHAP) -- Prime minister Yi 
Hoe-chang instructed relevant government offices on Thursday [21 
April] to obtain his approval of all unification-or national 
security-related policies referred to the Policy Coordination 
Council before they are put into practice. 
  "Since the Unification and National Security Policy 
Coordination Council is designed to review and adopt draft 
government policies, all policy matters referred to and decided 
by the council should now on be approved by the premier prior to 
their implementation," the premier said. 
  Kang Hyong-sok, the prime minister's spokesman, said Yi gave 
the instructions at his senior officials' meeting earlier in the 
day while stressing that all government policies should be 
drafted and determined through cabinet debate. 
  The premier stressed that it was unthinkable that, for 
instance, the policy of allowing North Korean loggers' 
resettlement in South Korea was released to the press before it 
was adopted at the cabinet level. 
  "Prime Minister Yi asked his secretariat to caution relevant 
government offices in this connection," the spokesman said. 
  Prime Minister Yi also told his staff to see to it that any 
expansion of mountain roads should be made in a way that does 
not damage environment, the spokesman said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

