<F P=102>   SK2204090094 Seoul YONHAP in English 0848 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2204090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 22 (YONHAP) -- The press secretary said 
Prime Minister Yi submitted his resignation to President Kim at 
Chongwadae [presidential office] on Friday afternoon. "I have 
nothing further to say," he said. 
  A stir had developed in the officialdom on Thursday when Yi 
told his senior officials to see to it that all policy items 
referred to the Unification and National Security Policy 
Coordination Council be implemented with advance approval by the 
prime minister. 
  Yi said it was unreasonable that a policy decision on North 
Korean loggers, for instance, was released to the press even 
before it was formally adopted at the cabinet level. 

