<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 22 (YONHAP) -- Deputy Prime Minister 
and National Unification Board [NUB] Minister Yi Yong-tok, was 
named the new prime minister Friday. 
  Following is his profile: 
  He was president of Myongji University and chairman of the 
administration's Public Service Ethics Committee before becoming 
the deputy prime minister and NUB minister in the cabinet 
reshuffle December 21 last year. 
  Born in North Korea, Yi, 68, has also served as vice 
president of the Korea National Red Cross and chief delegate to 
the inter-Korean Red Cross talks. He earned a doctorate of 
philosophy in education from Ohio State University. 

</TEXT>

