<H3> <TI>   Yi Yong-tok Pledges Devotion </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yi Yong-tok Pledges Devotion </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2204093994 Seoul YONHAP in English 0933 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2204093994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 22 (YONHAP) -- Prime Minister-designate 
Yi Yong-tok pledged Friday that he would do his utmost to serve 
the country and people if his appointment is legally approved by 
the National Assembly. 
  "I will see to it that the entire government becomes one 
under the leadership of the president and devote myself to live 
up to the responsibility bestowed upon me," Yi told reporters at 
his office in the National Unification Board [NUB] after his 
appointment was announced. 
  The NUB minister said the unification is possible once the 
people unite and continue with reforms to build a free country. 
  "Picturing a unified country, I will do my best to ensure 
freedom and welfare of the 70 million people of the Korean 
peninsula," he said. 
  He added that press reports about the intra-government 
confusion over unification and security-related policy were 
wrong. 

</TEXT>

