<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Singapore </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Goh Reviews European Trip </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Goh Reviews European Trip </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2104155694 Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation in 
English 1100 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2104155694 </F>
<F P=104>  Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong says his visits to 
Europe should be seen as a tying up of two ends of a ribbon. At 
one end are the prospects in the Asian economies and at the 
other end are prospective investors in Western Europe and 
elsewhere. Summing up his visits to Germany and Britain, Mr. 
Goh said Singapore wants to act as an intermediary to tie the 
knot. This is part of Singapore's overall strategy of going 
regional. The Singapore delegation's spokesman said Mr. Goh's 
trip to Germany had brought bilateral relations to a higher 
level. This is because of new steps being taken such as the 
formation of the Singapore-German Business Forum, the GSBF. 
  On Britain, the spokesman said the level of Singapore's 
relations with the country has been high. British leaders 
shared Mr. Goh's concern on the need to build on this 
relationship. One concrete way to assert the strengthened ties 
is through the setting up of the Singapore-British Business 
Council to be ready in about one to two months' time. 
  Mr. Goh returned home this evening after his official visits 
to Germany and Britain. 

</TEXT>

