<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leaders Support King's Roundtable Initiative </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Leaders Support King's Roundtable Initiative </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Backed by Ranariddh, Hun Sen </H4>

<F P=102> BK2304084194 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0447 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2304084194 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0447 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Message from the Royal Government to His Majesty King </F>
Norodom Sihanouk"; dated 22 April -- read by announcer] 
  [Text] Your Majesty: After receiving your 22 April 
statement, both of us, the first and second prime ministers of 
the Royal Government of Cambodia [RGC], would like to declare 
our support for your initiative to convene a roundtable meeting 
for peace and national reconciliation at the Royal Palace in 
Phnom Penh from 2 to 7 May 1994. We are ready to participate in 
the meeting to be held under Your Majesty's lofty chairmanship. 
  Your Majesty and revered queen, please accept our true 
loyalty and highest respects. 
  [Signed] First Prime Minister Norodom Ranariddh; Second 
Prime Minister Hun Sen. 
  [Dated] Phnom Penh, 22 April 1994. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-6764 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas079_i_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-079 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  23 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leaders Support King's Roundtable Initiative </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Leaders Support King's Roundtable Initiative </PHRASE></F></HT>
