<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Over 138,100 Hectares of Dry-Season Rice Planted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Over 138,100 Hectares of Dry-Season Rice Planted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2404142494 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1300 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2404142494 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1300 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the Agriculture Ministry, more than 
138,100 hectares of dry-season rice, or over 86 percent of the 
planned target, has been planted nationwide by 4 April. 
Outstanding provinces and cities in the planting effort 
included Takeo, Kandal, Prey Veng, and Kompong Cham Provinces. 
  The report also said that during this 1993-1994 dry season, 
our peasants planted 7,900 hectares of rice fewer than in the 
previous year. Many factors, such as [words indistinct] and 
late and prolonged harvest of rainy-season rice, delayed this 
year's dry-season rice planting. 
  During the same period, over 50,000 hectares of dry-season 
rice were harvested nationwide and the average yield was about 
two metric tons per hectare. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

