<F P=102>   SK2204135694 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1300 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2204135694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1300 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to reports from Seoul, U.S. Defense 
Secretary Perry made a junket [haenggak] to South Korea from 19 
to 21 April. 
  Perry's junket to South Korea was a junket of war to 
examine, 
on the spot, how their plan of a war of Northward aggression had 
been carried out and give new instructions to the puppets. 
  During the junket, Perry met with traitor Kim Yong-sam, 
puppet Defense Minister Yi Pyong-tae, and puppet Foreign 
Minister Han Sung-chu respectively, held one military confab 
[kunsajok moui] after another, mapped out vicious plans 
[hyunggye] to resume the Team Spirit joint military exercise 
before the end of this year, build up the U.S.-South Korea 
combined forces, strengthen the cooperation system, and pursue 
the UN Security Council sanctions [jeje] against the North. 
This is an unforgivable criminal act to bring the situation on 
the Korean peninsula to a crisis phase and cause a very 
dangerous situation. 

</TEXT>

