<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dailies Denounce Perry Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dailies Denounce Perry Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2304051194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0501 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2304051194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["U.S. Defense Secretary's Trip to South Korea Denounced" -- </F>
KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 23 (KCNA) -- Papers here today 
condemn the U.S. defense secretary's visit to South Korea as a 
war trip intended to unleash another war on the Korean 
peninsula, an aggressive trip to increase the military 
dependence of South Korea and a trip of plunder for fleecing the 
South Korean people through arms sale. 
  A NODONG SINMUN analyst, commenting on the war confabs Perry 
and the Kim Yong-sam group held with a view to doing harm to the 
DPRK, says: 
  Raving that the North would "invade the South" if sanctions 
are taken by the United Nations, the U.S. defense secretary 
described their military step as one intended to prevent it and 
made quite a noise as if it were the DPRK, not the United 
States, that violated the DPRK-USA agreed conclusions. 
  This is a jargon that could be uttered only by such 
warmaniacs as Perry who are accustomed to justifying their moves 
of aggression and war. It is the United States, not the DPRK, 
that failed to implement the agreed conclusions reached at the 
DPRK-USA contact in New York. 
  It goes without saying that the United States needed to mass 
its Armed Forces in South Korea, an alien land, only to provoke 
a war. 
  Perry decided to resume the "Team Spirit" war gamble with 
the 
puppets under unreasonable pretexts. This shows that they have 
no intention to seek a peaceful solution of the nuclear issue, 
and reveals his criminal intention to take the road of military 
adventure after massing U.S. Armed Forces on the Korean 
peninsula on the pretext of the North's "nuclear issue". Before 
setting foot in South Korea Perry sent Apache helicopters and 
Patriot missiles, and when he met with the puppets he pressured 
them to purchase heavy weapons of the United States, pressing 
home the need to build up the combat power of the U.S. forces 
and the puppet Army. 
  It is the intention of the United States to rake up colossal 
profits by forcing them to open not only the rice market but 
even the arms market of South Korea. 
  All this proves that the United States unilaterally 
discarded 
the Korean Armistice Agreement that prohibits the introduction 
of arms into South Korea for a war and the DPRK-USA joint 
statement on refraining from a nuclear threat to the DPRK and 
that the South Korean puppets nullified the North-South joint 
declaration on denuclearization that bans the introduction, 
deployment and production of nuclear weapons and are openly 
racing headlong along the road of war against the fellow 
countrymen. 
  The U.S. imperialists and the Kim Yong-sam puppet clique are 
recklessly trying to stifle the DPRK with "strength", but it is 
a miscalculation. 
  The United States must know clearly that military pressure 
or 
"sanctions" cannot work with the DPRK. 
  If the U.S. imperialists and the South Korean puppets 
finally 
push the situation on the Korean peninsula to a dangerous phase 
of war, they would be unable to escape a thousand-fold blow. 
  A MINJU CHOSON analyst warns that the aggressors and the 
traitors must act not rashly but prudently, clearly mindful of 
what tragic consequences their war frenzy would bring to them. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

