<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Conducts `Aerial Mobile Deployment' Exercise </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Conducts `Aerial Mobile Deployment' Exercise </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2304040194 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1200 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2304040194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1200 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to military sources, the U.S. imperialists 
conducted aerial mobile deployment exercises on 21 April by 
flying various aircraft, including fighter-bomber planes loaded 
with nuclear weapons, to South Korea from its overseas bases. 
  On 21 April, some 10 fighter-bomber planes, pursuit-assault 
planes, and vertical take-off and landing attack planes loaded 
with nuclear weapons took off from Okinawa and Yokosuka bases in 
Japan for deployment to the U.S. Air Force bases occupying South 
Korea. The frantic war exercise was aimed at evaluating a speedy 
deployment to the Korean peninsula and actual fighting 
deployment capabilities. 
  On the other hand, on 20 April, KC-135 refueling planes flew 
from overseas bases over the sea off Kunsan, South Korea, and 
were frenzied with war fever by refueling tens of fighter-bomber 
planes and pursuit-assault planes, which were running wild in 
night aerial war exercises, from 1900 [1000 GMT] to 2200 [1300 
GMT]. 
  On 21 April, the South Korean puppets frantically exercised 
gun firing and helicopter sorties right in front of our nose 
near the DMZ. That day, 105-mm large-caliber artillery groups, 
which occupied firing positions in Naedae-ri, Chorwon County, 
Kangwon Province, and Magori, Yonchon County, Kyonggi Province 
in South Korea, fired tens of bomb shells near the DMZ. The 
puppet Army's armed gangsters, which occupied combat positions 
in Yongsan-ri, Paju County, Kyonggi Province, and Kangsan-ri and 
Yangjae-ri, Chorwon County in the South Korean Kangwon Province, 
wielded a horrible war frenzy by randomly shooting some 1,000 
shots of large-caliber machine guns. 
  In addition, on the same day, the puppet Army's armed 
helicopters and transport helicopters ran wild in exercising 
ground support and air transport in the skies over areas 
adjacent to Pochon, Yonchon, and Chorwon of the South Korean 
Kangwon Province. 
  The fire game commotion of the U.S. imperialists and South 
Korean puppets is further aggravating the war risk on the Korean 
peninsula. 

</TEXT>

