<F P=102>   SK2204152794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1517 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2204152794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the 
Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of 
Korea (GFTUK) in a statement today denounced the South Korean 
authorities's negative stand toward the DPRK's proposal for the 
convocation of a national conference and urged them to look 
straight at the nation's aspirations and respond to the proposal. 
  Noting that the South Korean authorities showed a negative 
response to the proposal, saying "a conference oriented toward 
political propaganda is undesirable", the spokesman says this 
fully reveals their true color as flunkeyist traitors trying to 
plunge the nation into the scourge of war in league with outside 
forces, instead of sitting at a negotiating table with fellow 
countrymen to solve the question of national reunification 
independently. 
  He said, "Our working class and the whole nation can never 
tolerate the criminal moves of the Kim Yong-sam group which is 
taking the extremely dangerous road to a nuclear war in league 
with outside forces, disregarding the proposal for the 
convocation of a national conference which was prompted by our 
warm love of the nation and the stand of national independence 
to bridge over the present difficulties and open a broad avenue 
for reunification through the great unity of the nation." 
  "The South Korean authorities must immediately remove the 
checkbar which they dropped on the road ahead of the political 
parties, organizations and personages of broad strata in South 
Korea intending to participate in a national conference," the 
spokesman said. 
  He called upon all the workers and other sections of people 
of South Korea to actively turn out in a patriotic struggle for 
the convocation of a national conference which would open up a 
short cut to reunification in the '90s. 

</TEXT>

