<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Envoy Asks UN To Save Gorazde From Attacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2204155394 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1500 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2204155394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Indonesia has asked the UN Security Council to 
take decisive action to save Gorazde, one of the UN-designated 
safe havens in Bosnia, from the Serbian attacks. Speaking at a 
formal meeting of the UN Security Council in New York, Nugroho 
Wisnumurti, Indonesian permanent representative to the United 
Nations, said the status of Gorazde and other safe havens must 
be upheld and the arms embargo against Bosnia-Herzegovina lifted. 
  Nugroho said a new diplomatic initiative aimed at reaching a 
cease-fire in Gorazde and the entire territory of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina must continue so as to find a political 
settlement to the conflict. He also stressed the importance of 
ensuring the safety and independence of the UN personnel serving 
in Bosnia. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

