  [Text] Indonesia hopes that the PRC Government does not 
doubt its determination and ability to swiftly cope with the 
riots in Medan, North Sumatera, which have threatened the safety 
of the ethnic Chinese community. 
  Foreign Minister Ali Alatas said this in Jakarta today in 
response to a statement issued by (Wu Chiaming), spokesman of 
the PRC Foreign Ministry, calling on the Indonesian Government 
to immediately curb the demonstrations by workers in Medan which 
led to anti-Chinese riots. 
  The Indonesian Government's determination to deal with the 
riots was reflected in the remarks by President Suharto and 
other high-ranking officials who sought to take strong action 
against the rioters because the demonstrations led to 
destruction acts based on the sensitive SARA [tribal, religious, 
racial, and intergrouping conflicts] issues. 

