25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2504094794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  Thai </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Squadron Leader Prasong Sunsiri 
told reporters that he received a phone call from Cambodian 
Foreign Minister Samdech Kromkhun Norodom Sirivut this morning 
to inform him that the Cambodian Government plans to organize a 
roundtable meeting with representatives of all Cambodian 
factions on 2 May. The Cambodian foreign minister said that the 
Cambodian Government, with its intention to clear up any 
skepticism regarding Thailand and create mutual better 
understanding between the two countries, one of the issues to be 
raised for discussion during the meeting will be the alleged 
Thai assistance to the Khmer Rouge. 
  Touching on the plight of some 1,000 displaced Cambodians 
who 
fled the fighting in Cambodia to take refuge in Ta Phraya 
District of Sakeo Province, the Cambodian foreign minister said 
that Cambodian officials in collaboration with the Office of the 
UN High Commissioner for Refugees will take care of them. In 
this regard, Squadron Prasong Sunsiri informed his Cambodian 
counterpart that Thailand has not pushed any displaced people 
out of the country. However, if they return to Cambodia, they do 
so on a voluntary basis. 

</TEXT>

