<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   DP Backs Down From Demand </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DP Backs Down From Demand </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2504071294 Seoul YONHAP in English 0645 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2504071294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 25 (YONHAP) -- The opposition 
Democratic Party (DP) decided Monday to withdraw its demand for 
the government to form a coalition cabinet. 
  Kim Won-ki, a member of the party's supreme committee, said 
the panel had discussed the demand, which party chairman Yi 
Ki-taek expressed to reporters on the plane carrying him back 
from the United States, and agreed to cancel it. 
  "We talked about the coalition cabinet but reached the 
conclusion that this is not the appropriate time to make such a 
demand. Our party has no plans to mention the demand anymore," 
he said. 
  Chairman Yi had urged President Kim Yong-sam to disband his 
cabinet, set up a pan-national crisis management organ and form 
a coalition cabinet. 

</TEXT>

