BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 25 KYODO -- Tsutomu Hata, 58, leader of 
Shinseito, was elected Japan's new prime minister Monday by the 
House of Representatives, succeeding Morihiro Hosokawa, whose 
coalition cabinet resigned earlier in the day. 

</TEXT>

