<H3> <TI>   Insurance Group Considers Private-Sector Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Insurance Group Considers Private-Sector Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2304142094 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 22 Apr 
94 Morning Edition p 7--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2304142094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 21 April, Takashi Onoda, chairman of the Marine 
and Fire Insurance Association of Japan, Inc. [MFIAJ], in 
reference to the fact that the insurance sector has become one 
of the focal points in the Japan-U.S. framework trade talks, 
said: "We are considering plans to set up a meeting ground 
where officials from the private sector can hold discussions to 
deepen their mutual understanding." Onoda, who is also 
president of the Sumitomo Marine and Fire Insurance Co. Ltd., 
made the comment at a news conference held the same day. He 
also disclosed there are plans to revise the existing system to 
give easier access to membership in the MFIAJ for foreign 
insurance companies which have entered the Japanese market. 
  The MFIAJ already holds meetings with foreign insurance 
companies which have entered the Japanese market. Onoda, 
however, feels these meetings have remained too routine. He 
disclosed the MFIAJ is thus considering plans to set up a forum 
where top-level meetings can be held to discuss a broad range of 
topics. The plans are expected to materialize as early as this 
coming summer. 

</TEXT>

