<H3> <TI>   Agenda for Planned Fujii-Bentsen Talks Reviewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agenda for Planned Fujii-Bentsen Talks Reviewed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2304032694 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 23 
Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2304032694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 23 April Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] On 22 April, a Foreign Ministry source indicated 
that Finance Minister Hirohisa Fujii and Treasury Secretary 
Lloyd Bentsen are expected to hold Japanese-U.S. finance 
ministerial talks in Washington prior to a meeting of finance 
ministers and central bank governors from the Group of Seven 
(G-7) major industrialized nations which is to be held there. 
Although a concrete schedule for the Fujii-Bentsen meeting has 
not yet been decided on, on 23 April both sides were 
coordinating the schedule. 
  During the meeting with Bentsen, Fujii is expected to 
indicate the government's intention to maintain in the future 
its basic position on Japan's policies toward foreign countries 
and its domestic economic measures, as well on following a 
policy accord reached by the ruling coalition parties. 
Meanwhile, Bentsen is expected to call for additional economic 
pump-priming measures by Japan, claiming that "Japan should make 
voluntary efforts to achieve an economic recovery led by the 
expansion of domestic demand to lead a world economic recovery." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

