<H3> <TI>   Hata Applauds DPRK Move on IAEA Inspectors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hata Applauds DPRK Move on IAEA Inspectors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2304024594 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 23 
Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2304024594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 22 April Evening Edition] </F>
  [Text] The DPRK (North Korea) has softened its hardline 
stand on the nuclear issue by notifying the International Atomic 
Energy Agency (IAEA) that it will allow IAEA inspectors to 
observe the replacement of fuel rods in an experimental reactor. 
Commenting on the North Korean proposal, Tsutomu Hata, deputy 
prime minister and foreign minister, said at a news conference 
on 22 April after a cabinet meeting that "this is something we 
have to welcome." At the news conference, the foreign minister 
also reiterated, "It is important for North Korea to explain 
things candidly [about its suspected nuclear weapons program] to 
the international community." 

</TEXT>

