<H3> <TI>   ROK Economic Partnership Talks Open in Seoul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ROK Economic Partnership Talks Open in Seoul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2304010494 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 22 Apr 
94 Morning Edition p 5--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2304010494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Takashi Hiranuma] </F>
  [Text] Seoul, 21 April -- The Japanese and South Korean 
Governments opened the first Japanese-ROK economic partnership 
conference in Seoul on 21 April. The Japanese side is 
represented by Deputy Vice Foreign Minister Sadayuki Hayashi, 
while his South Korean counterpart is Son Chun-yong, second 
deputy vice foreign minister. Each side has about 20 
working-level officials altogether from its ministries concerned 
with economic affairs attending the meeting. A wide-ranging 
exchange of views is being held on bilateral economic 
cooperation. The conference is scheduled to be held on 21 and 
22 April. 
  This conference is being held in accordance with an 
agreement 
reached at the Japanese-ROK summit meeting in Kyongju, South 
Korea, in November 1993. The conference was formed by 
reorganizing the previously existing Japanese-ROK Trade, 
Business, and Technological Cooperation Committee. 

</TEXT>

