<H3> <TI>   UNHCR Backs Tokyo Bid for Seat on UNSC </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNHCR Backs Tokyo Bid for Seat on UNSC </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2304112194 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 22 Apr 94 
Morning Edition p 3--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2304112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 21 April, Sadako Ogata, UN High Commissioner for 
Refugees (UNHCR), touched on the issue of Japan's bid for a 
permanent seat in the UN Security Council [UNSC], and said: 
"There are various opinions in Japan, but I feel it is natural 
for Japan to be in the UNSC. This view has become widespread 
within the United Nations. Regarding Japan's contributions, 
however, it would be difficult for Japan to feel it is actually 
making contributions unless it actually participates in UN 
activities." Ogata, who is temporarily back in Japan, made the 
comments in response to a question by an ASASHI SHIMBUN 
reporter. She added: "It is desired that Japan participate in 
activities in diverse ways, whether it be refugee problems or 
development assistance programs. What is important is a 
willingness to actively contribute in areas where Japan can do 
its best." 

</TEXT>

