<H3> <TI>   MOF Official Rebuts Hosokawa's Criticisms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MOF Official Rebuts Hosokawa's Criticisms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2304010394 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 22 Apr 94 
Morning Edition p 11--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2304010394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Looking back at the disturbances created over the 
issue of the national welfare tax, Prime Minister Morihiro 
Hosokawa said at a dinner meeting with Chief Cabinet Secretary 
Masayoshi Takemura and Deputy Chief Cabinet Secretary Yukio 
Hatoyama on the evening of 20 April that "the Ministry of 
Finance [MOF] took advantage of me." In this regard, Jiro 
Saito, administrative vice finance minister, made a comment at a 
news conference on 21 April and smiled wryly, saying, "I have no 
knowledge of taking advantage of the prime minister." He even 
looked angry for a moment. 
  The prime minister reportedly said: "I wanted to use the 
power of the MOF. On the contrary, however, the ministry took 
advantage of me over the issue of the national welfare tax and 
other issues." The prime minister reportedly did some 
soul-searching at a midnight news conference as well. He 
sounded as if he was saying he failed because he acted in 
accordance with the MOF's recommendations. 
  In this regard, Saito first said "I think I should not 
comment on this because I heard it from others." He then denied 
a rumor that "the Ministry of Finance masterminded the national 
welfare tax plan." 

</TEXT>

