<H3> <TI>   Ozawa Views Cooperation With LDP's Watanabe </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ozawa Views Cooperation With LDP's Watanabe </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2304055894 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 23 
Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2304055894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 23 April Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] Ichiro Ozawa, Shinseito [Japan Renewal Party] 
secretary general, commented on his cooperation with Liberal 
Democratic Party [LDP] member Michio Watanabe, former deputy 
prime minister and foreign minister, in a Fuji Television 
program on 22 April. Ozawa indicated his intention to continue 
to seek a cooperative relationship with Watanabe in the future 
on the condition that Watanabe leaves the LDP. He said: 
"Allying with the LDP runs counter to our spirit (and our ideas 
upon forming Shinseito). However, I still hope to act with him 
if he secedes from the LDP." 
  In criticizing the idea of "forming a coalition between the 
LDP and the Social Democratic Party of Japan" while excluding 
Shinseito, which is an idea that once cropped up in the process 
of establishing the next administration, Ozawa stated, "This 
concept lacks the right recognition of the times." In warning 
these parties, Ozawa said: "This is nothing other than a 
suicidal act. Why do they want to do this?" 

</TEXT>

