  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 22 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
situation concerning the political hunger strike has not been 
settled down yet. For nine days goes on the hunger strike of 
members and supporters of the Mongolian Democratic Association, 
the Union of Mongolian Students and Union for New Progress 
demanding resignation of the government. The counter strike for 
support of the government is lasting for six days. 
  Yesterday rallies were held called by fighting political 
forces. The meeting at the central square of the Mongolian 
capital was ended in scanning by its participants the appeals 
for resignation of the government and marching around the state 
residence. As for the meeting called by the public organization 
"281 Union" at the Erh Choloonii Square it has gone off rather 
quietly with a few participants. 

