<H3> <TI>   Hural To Draft Laws on Protests, Corruption </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hural To Draft Laws on Protests, Corruption </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2204145794 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1302 GMT 22 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2204145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 22 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Proceeding 
from the recommendations made by the Council for Ensuring the 
National Security and based upon the political concord reached 
yesterday between the general secretary of the Mongolian 
People's Revolutionary Party and the leader of the Mongolian 
National Democratic Party and the head of the Mongolian 
Social-Democratic Party, the Great State Hural of Mongolia has 
passed late in night a decision aimed to regulate the 
complicated political situation arisen over the last days in 
Mongolia and settle down the burning questions. 
  The Mongolian parliament has decided to consider by its 
spring session the draft laws on the procedure of carrying out 
demonstrations and meetings, the struggle against corruption as 
well as the draft law on freedom of press and information which 
is to be submitted for consideration on the initiative of the 
president of Mongolia. The parliament has charged the 
government to present for consideration at the spring session of 
1994 the report on the issues concerning the social economic 
situation of the country. 
  The government has been charged to work out and submit for 
discussion by the parliament within the year 1994 the drafts of 
laws on ethic standards for highest political holders of 
position and the nationwide referendum to be carried out. 

</TEXT>

