<H3> <TI>   Seminar Held on Constitutional Court </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Seminar Held on Constitutional Court </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2204143694 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1327 GMT 22 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2204143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 22 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
participants of the seminar on the issues of legislative 
strengthening of the activities of the Constitutional Court of 
Mongolia organized by the Mongolian section on human rights and 
the permanent representative of the US Asian Fund for 
Development in Mongolia have agreed to a common opinion on 
necessity to strengthen legislatively the activities of the body 
for enforcing the constitutional control. Such a conclusion was 
derived by the specialists-lawyers, members of the 
Constitutional Court and the Mongolian parliament taking part in 
this seminar after their acquainting and discussing the reports 
which were put on the agenda. It should be noted that the accent 
was put on that amendments and changes to the law on 
Constitutional Court should be made within the frameworks of the 
Constitution of the country the materials of the seminar as has 
been noted prior to this would be presented afterwards in the 
form of recommendations to the working group on elaborating the 
draft law on changes and amendments to be made to the 
legislation on the Constitutional Court. [sentence as received] 
  The seminar was carried out in a two staged form. Firstly 
after the opening ceremony of the seminar there were presented 
the major reports relating to the problem then on a weekly 
interval the work of the seminar was continued so that the 
participants would have been provided with proper possibilities 
to scrutinize and think them over and arrive at proper 
conclusions during this spell of time. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

