<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daily Cites U.S., IAEA `Unreasonable' Demand </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily Cites U.S., IAEA `Unreasonable' Demand </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2504051994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0507 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2504051994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Unreasonable Demand Cannot Be Met" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN today 
brands the demand of the United States and the International 
Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] for the DPRK's full compliance with 
the safeguards agreement, which was contained in a "presidential 
statement" of the U.N. Security Council, as unjustifiable and 
unreasonable. 
  The news analyst says: 
  Their demand ignoring the DPRK's unique status following the 
temporary suspension of the effectuation of its announced 
withdrawal from the Non-proliferation Treaty shows they are 
trying to deny the unique status of the DPRK and use the 
safeguards agreement as an experient for the sinister political 
purpose of stifling it. 
  We cannot fully comply with the safeguards agreement, even 
if 
we try before the United States and the IAEA prove in practice 
that they are not going to stifle the DPRK. 
  So long as the United States refuses to stop the anti-DPRK 
campaign and its nuclear threat and the IAEA Secretariat fails 
to renounce its partiality, we cannot allow inspection 
activities tantamount to routine and ad hoc inspections. 
  It is self-evident that if we allow such inspection 
activities while the IAEA is escalating its partiality, 
dishonest officials of the IAEA Secretariat will join-more 
zealously in the U.S. policy of stifling the DPRK, groundlessly 
charging us with the possession of something which we do not 
have, and reversing black and white. 
  When the United States and the IAEA Secretariat respect our 
unique status, the nuclear issue will be settled smoothly. 
  How long our unique status lasts depends on the behavior of 
the United States and the IAEA Secretariat. 
  Pressure cannot be a solution to the problem. 
  It is our consistent position to resolve the nuclear issue 
peacefully through dialogue and negotiation. 
  It is entirely up to the United States and the IAEA 
Secretariat how the situation will develop. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-6889 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas079_c_94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-079 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  22 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Radio Denounces Patriot Deployment to Front Line </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radio Denounces Patriot Deployment to Front Line </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2204131494 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1213 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2204131494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1213 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to Seoul KBS-1 Radio, on 21 April the 
U.S. imperialists finally began to deploy new-model Patriot 
missiles to the central region of the front line in South Korea, 
despite strong protest and denunciation by the Korean people and 
by a broad range of world public opinion. This is an open 
challenge to us and is aimed at threatening us militarily and 
carrying out a preemptive strike against the Northern half of 
the Republic. 
  The beginning of the U.S. deployment of new-model Patriot 
missiles to the central region of the front line while talking 
about a nonexisting offensive threat by someone else is a 
deliberate, dangerous military act [uidojogin wihomhan kunsa 
haengdong] to make the situation on the Korean peninsula more 
unstable [touk puranjonghage hago], and further, to prompt 
[yubal] a new war. 
  The deployment of new-model Patriot missiles in broad 
daylight plainly shows that the U.S. authorities can cast any 
international agreement away like dirt to achieve their goal of 
aggression, taking no regard of the Armistice Agreement or the 
armistice organization. 
  The U.S. imperialists should discreetly act, being well 
aware 
what grave consequence will result from the deployment of 
new-model Patriot missiles, which pose a great threat to the 
peace and security of Korean peninsula and the Far East. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-6890 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas079_l_94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-079 </AU>
Daily Report 
