<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kang Sok-chu on DPRK-U.S. Working Contact </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kang Sok-chu on DPRK-U.S. Working Contact </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2304090794 Seoul TONG-A ILBO in Korean 23 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK2304090794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul TONG-A ILBO </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In a letter sent to Robert Gallucci, U.S. assistant 
secretary of State, Kang Sok-chu, North Korean vice foreign 
minister, proposed a working-level contact to prepare for the 
third round of North Korean-U.S. high-level talks. This was 
revealed by a relevant government official on 22 April. 
  On 22 April, the government official said that "Vice 
Minister 
Kang sent a letter to Assistant Secretary Gallucci on 19 April 
and revealed the willingness to allow the presence of an 
inspection team from the International Atomic Energy Agency when 
nuclear fuel rods are replaced at a five-megawatt nuclear 
reactor in Yongbyon, and proposed holding a working-level 
contact." The government official then added that "the 
working-level contact is expected to be held during next week." 

</TEXT>

