<F P=101> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<H3> <TI>   Contingency Plan for Bosnia on Draft Board </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Contingency Plan for Bosnia on Draft Board </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2504104594 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0600 
GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2504104594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Defense Minister Datuk Sri Najib Tun Razak said the 
Malaysian Armed Forces is drafting a contingency plan for its 
peacekeepers in Bosnia-Herzegovina to meet any eventuality due 
to worsening situation there. He said the plan included steps 
to be taken to ensure the safety of the Malaysian troops serving 
with the United Nations Protection Force -- UNPROFOR -- in the 
war-torn country. He said the Defense Ministry will ensure that 
the Malaysian Battalion -- Malbatt -- members in Bosnia to be 
prepared to meet any eventuality, including attacks from the 
Serbs. 
  Datuk Sri Najib was speaking to reporters after opening an 
UMNO [United Malays National Organization] seminar in Kerteh in 
the state of Negeri Sembilan. He said but to do this Malaysia 
needs the approval of the United Nations. Datuk Sri Najib said 
so long as Malbatt was [words indistinct], the Malaysian 
soldiers in Bosnia- Herzegovina were bound by a UN guideline. 

</TEXT>

